Tbh I don't know if used the right Item ID's in the interface, if I didn't then change the ID's on your own.

[b]Tutorial: Adding a Skill Menu[/b]
[b]Tested on: iClarity[/b]
[b]Difficulty: 1/10[/b]
[b]Requirments: None
[/b]
[b]Classes edited: client/clientHandler class, ActionButtons/clickingMost class[/b]

[b]Step 1:[/b]
Open your client/clientHandler class(client.java/clientHandler.java)


Below:
[code]public class clientHandler extends Player implements Runnable {[/code]


Add this:

[code]

public void attackinterface() {
		sendFrame126("@dre@Attack Interface", 8716);
		for(int i = 8720;i<8799;i++) {
			sendFrame126("",i);
		}
		sendFrame126("1",8720);
		sendFrame126("Bronze",8760);
		sendFrame126("1",8721);
		sendFrame126("Iron", 8761);
		sendFrame126("5",8722);
		sendFrame126("Steel",8762);
		sendFrame126("10",8723);
		sendFrame126("Black", 8763);
		sendFrame126("20",8724);
		sendFrame126("Mithril", 8764);
		sendFrame126("30",8725);
		sendFrame126("Adamant",8765);
		sendFrame126("40",8726);
		sendFrame126("Rune", 8766);
		sendFrame126("60",8727);
		sendFrame126("Dragon", 8767);
		sendFrame126("70", 8728);
		sendFrame126("Barrows", 8768);
		sendFrame126("",8849);
		sendFrame126("",8827);
		sendFrame126("",8837);
		sendFrame126("",8840);
		sendFrame126("",8843);
		sendFrame126("",8846); 
		sendFrame126("",8823);
		sendFrame126("",8824);
		sendFrame126("",8859);
		sendFrame126("",8862);
		sendFrame126("",8865);
		sendFrame126("",15303);
		sendFrame126("",15306);
		sendFrame126("",15309);

		sendFrame34(8847,1277,0,1);
		sendFrame34(8847,1279,1,1);
		sendFrame34(8847,1281,2,1);
		sendFrame34(8847,1283,3,1);
        	sendFrame34(8847,1285,4,1);
		sendFrame34(8847,1287,5,1);
    		sendFrame34(8847,1289,6,1);
		sendFrame34(8847,1305,7,1);
    		sendFrame34(8847,4726,8,1);
		showInterface(8714);
}[/code]


This is going to write the level required to wear Bronze in the Menu
[code]sendFrame126("1",8720);[/code]


This will be placed close to the Bronze Swords picture
[code]sendFrame126("Bronze",8760);[/code]


1277 = Bronze Sword ID, going to show in the menu the Bronze Sword
[code]sendFrame34(8847,1277,0,1);[/code]


[b]Step 2:[/b]
Open your ActionButtons/clickingMost class(ActionButtons.java/clickingMost.java)
and search for:
[code]switch (actionButtonId) {[/code]


Below add:

[code]

case 33206:
p.attackinterface();
break;
[/code]


So by clicking on the Attack button(33206 ID), the attackinterface will pop-up
[code]case 33206:
p.attackinterface();
[/code]


That`s it.


